<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>The @@@D2Dream@@@ Zealot Paladin is a slight twist on the classic fast hitting melee character. He utilizes the runewords @@@D2Dream@@@ to adjust his attacks from being purely physical to adding in lightning Damage. This gives him a little bit more coverage in the monsters he fights and overall is just simply a different style of the Zealot. A strong melee character that can play through a lot of PvE content but does require some gear setup first.</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the @@@D2Dream@@@ Zealot. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>NOTE: You will either be running @@@D2Fanaticism@@@ or @@@D2Conviction@@@. Both have pros and cons and depend on your gear. Also we do not skill @@@D2HolyShock@@@, the synergy points are for the auras from the Items.</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2ResistLightning@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2HolyShock@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Salvation@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2HolyShock@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Sacrifice@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2Zeal@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Zeal@@@ - Main Damage dealer, invest in @@@D2Sacrifice@@@ first for more Damage or @@@D2Zeal@@@ for more attack rating, required</li>
<li>1+ points to @@@D2HolyShield@@@ - Great for Max Block, required</li>
</ol>

